## ECE 271B — Age Classification under Occlusion

Age group classification on UTKFace under synthetic occlusions using classical methods and deep models.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Team

- Alexander Tung  
- Alexander Wang  
- Luke Wittemann  

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Setup

Create a virtual environment and install dependencies:

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Set the UTKFace dataset path in:
configs/default.yaml

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Run Experiments

python -m scripts.train_eval_pca_gaussian
python -m scripts.train_eval_lda_gaussian
python -m scripts.train_eval_kpca_svm
python -m scripts.train_eval_cnn
python -m scripts.train_eval_mlp

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Outputs

Results: outputs/results/*.json
Models: outputs/models/

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Notes

- Task: Age prediction is formulated as 3-class binned classification (1-9, 10-19, 20-29).

- Training protocol: All models train on clean faces and are evaluated under occlusion.

- Occlusion types: none, eyes, mouth, center.

- Class imbalance: Dataset is skewed toward the oldest age bin (roughly 73% are age 20-29 images), so macro-F1 is the primary metric.

- PCA: Uses whitening to stabilize the Gaussian classifier.

- LDA: Output dimension is automatically ≤ (C − 1).

- CNN: Uses ImageNet-pretrained ResNet-18 backbone.

- Reproducibility: Global seed is controlled in configs/default.yaml.
